title: For Sale:  Lithgow #1 Mark III ENFIELD Rifle - 99% Condition!!!!
postcontent:
This is an Enfield #1 Mark III rifle that I purchased many years ago. Since then I've had it out of lockup about a half dozen times and I have shot it. However for the vast majority of the time it's been stored in a dehumidified safe.

Rifle's  receiver is marked "Lithgow SHT.LE III - 1931". The overall condition of this rifle is nearly perfect - both metal & wood. There are only the slightest handling/storage marks and you'd really have to examine the rifle carefully to see them. The bore is excellent as well. Overall I'd put the rifle's condition at 99%. As you would expect the chambering is .303 British.

Rifle comes with an original Enfield military cleaning kit, bolt disassembly tool, two khaki color WWII vintage slings. Plus an original British bandoleer complete with 50 rounds of clean surplus .303 ammo loaded on 10 original Enfield stripper clips. 

Additionally, there is a high quality reproduction 1907 pattern, hooked quillion bayonet. I bought this several years ago from IMA and it was their Grade 1 (collector grade) model. I decided on this after looking at many original bayonets which were all beat up and just didn't match this beautiful rifle. Then finally there is a  high quality reproduction khaki color Enfield case. It's made of very heavy canvas just like the original, and it has a separate pocket to carry the cleaning kit & tools. The rear of the case has two sewn in eyelets that the second sling (included) attaches to that enables the case to be shoulder carried. 

Asking price for everything is $850. Transaction is FTF with pickup in the Brandon, FL area. You must be a Florida resident and at least 21 to purchase. A proper bill of sale will be provided.

title: For Sale:  HK Style 26.5mm Flare Pistol w/.22LR Adapter & accessories
postcontent:
This is a Polish 26.5mm Flare Pistol made in 1985. My inspection showed that it is essentially an exact copy of the HK P2A1. 

 It's in very condition with at least 95% of it's bluing intact. There is some slight loss of blue around the muzzle and where the action rode in the holster. The bore is  excellent and function is perfect. Pistol is well marked with the Circle 11 symbol that designates it as produced at Radom Arsenal, Poland so no question that it's high quality. I suspect that HK must have licensed their P2A1 to Radom because the two are virtually identical. 

Comes with an original carry bag/holster with shoulder strap that's in good condition. Also included is a 26.5mm size cleaning rod & original rope style lanyard.  Finally there is a brand new Sub-caliber Adapter that allows any .22LR ammo to be safely fired from this flare pistol. Note that once the adapter is dropped into the pistol that it does become a real firearm that must be treated accordingly. 

$125 with pickup in the Brandon/Valrico area. Must be 21 or older to purchase. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Benifet Match for Terry McClure, Gun Give away
postcontent:
Start time: 9am. End time and drawing for giveaways approximately 2pm.
Lunch will be available at the match.
_Schedule is set but small changes of times or small events may change slightly depending on times and interest of certain events at the match. Limited amount of ammo for donated firearms is available so if you have ammunition (BRASS CASED) then please bring it so that others who don’t have access to the ammunition have a chance to shoot as well.
_ Due to the amount of shooting events going on there will be NO picking up of brass in the bays until all events of the day are done. After the end of the matches and drawings if you wish to pick up your brass you can. Please pick up only the approximate amount of brass that was yours. We understand that brass is needed by shooters please be honest! Please only pick up the caliber you brought and shot at the range. 
_Stages in bay 1,2 & 3 are $15 for the three stages or $5 per stage. Fee will also include a Ticket for prize table. 
_9am-12pm: Two IDPA style stages in bay 1&2. These stages will be pistol and Carbine Stages (your choice of firearm used).  Bay 3 is a USPSA stage set up and provided by Nicks Pawn Shop in Salina. To shoot stages more than once each additional shooting of a stage is $5. If you do not have a pistol or wish to shoot a donated firearm there will be some available. In this case you will need to bring brass cased ammunition or you can pay for ammunition provided by the donator. (Please no steel cased ammunition for hand guns if you are bringing your own ammo to shoot in a donated gun). 
_9am-12pm: Sharps Rifle silhouette shoot. This is an open sight buffalo rifle donated by MI-TE Bullets. Price is $3 a shot and each hit on the target will win you tickets for the prize table give away. 100 rounds available so if ammo is spent before 12pm then another event may be put in place.
_9am-12pm: Carbine 100+ yard shooting. Price will vary per shot depending on Donator or if shooting your own. Caliber limit is .223 or 7.62x39. Hits on target will result in winning of prize table tickets.   
_12pm-2pm approximately: Pistol races will be a challenge of speed vs accuracy. This will consist of bowling pins, steel and maybe something else to boot! This will be a bracket race with buy backs. 5$ to enter the bracket. First two round eliminations allow a $5 buy back. After first two rounds no buy backs allowed. This will be a head to head race and first to eliminate each target and finish will move on to the next round until a winner prevails.
_Afterwards will be a shot gun race. This will be similar to bowling pin race but will not consist of bowling pins. Price is $5 to enter the bracket. First two round buy backs allowed for $5. Each race will force a reload. This will help everyone to play on a level playing field with a whole lot of fun and laughs. Why enter the race and buy back if your eliminated in first two rounds? Winners of races will have first choice at prize table. Winner of races will have a match up head to head with a donated firearm for battle of first choice at prize table. Some prizes valued up to $250. 
_As stated before depending on time and interest of an event small changes may be made. There will be a chance to shoot a donated firearm in a simple stage set up for first time shooters or shooters who want to shoot different types of pistols or fire arms in a simple stage set up. 
_Activities for children will be available and responsible volunteer’s will be there to see to it that your children have proper supervision and can have fun and play time with other children. We are a family oriented club with a play area for children. So often anti-gun individuals perceive us shooters in a negative way. But as Legal Gun Owners and Law abiding citizens we are about safety 1st, 2nd is having fun with sporting rifles, pistols, shotguns etc. So bring the kids and the whole family and meet our family of shooters and a man who dedicated so much of his life to others!
_Special Thanks to the Sponsors & Businesses who donated and helped out. Also thanks to the individual shooters and other people who do not know Terry but wanted to donate and help out any way. This is what our club and Shooters across KS and the nation should be about. Not only having fun but helping others in need! Thank you!!!
_Sponsors & Donators: CKPS, Fusion Firearms, MI-TE Bullets, Nicks Pawn Shop, Dawson Precision, Midway USA, Bobs Pawn Shop, Brownells, W.C.  and any others that may be acquired this week. (Check www.kspistol.com) for updates.
_Gun Give Away: $10 Donation per ticket. Bushmaster Lightweight AR with 100 rounds of .223 ammo. S&W m&p 22 pistol with 225 rounds of ammo. You do not have to be present at drawing to win the firearms.  FFL Transfer/background check through MI-TE Bullets.
_Donated Prize table items: CKPS 1 year membership, (2) Fusion $250 gift cert. for custom work, MI-TE Bullets Cast Bullets, (2) sets Dawson P sights for Glocks, (5) boxes of 1000ct. CCI primers from Nicks, Brownells Leather Range Bag, Wilson Combat %20 off FIREARMS or any accessories, Midway $25 gift cert., Knives-Binoculars-flashlight from Bobs Pawn. Individual Donations: 9mm .45acp, 22lr, 12 gauge and more caliber ammunition, (3) Tripp 1911 mags, Pistol case, Exploding rifle target and more. If you are wanting to donate any accessories or ammo for the prize table you can bring it to the match. All proceeds go to Terry McClure and his family. Terry has given so much to many of us and served as law enforcement for 20+ years. Diagnosed with ALS he had to retire and move and requires help each day. He is now in need of our help and every penny raised will help his family. So please come and meet Terry, Have some fun and donate while having a great time!

title: For Sale:  LNIB Leupold VX-R 4-12x40 Illuminated Duplex Reticle CDS
postcontent:
I am selling my like-new Leupold VX-R complete with 30mm tube.  Sale includes original box, paperwork, Leupold sunshade tube (~4") and Leupold front flip-cover.  The only reason I am selling is to get a higher-magnification Leupold Mark 4, and I don't have another rifle that needs a scope.

The illuminated "FireDot" duplex reticle is the primary reason I chose the VX-R.  The brightness can be adjusted to several levels, extending your shooting capability in low-light conditions even on the bench test when it starts getting dark.  The scope also has a great tactical look and solid feel.

This VX-R is the CDS or "Custom Dial System" version that allows you to send your rifle/ammo specs to Leupold and they customize a ballistic drop turret for you, giving you an immense advantage in timed shooting competitions.  I never sent in for mine (been working on rifle break-in) so you can send off and customize this scope to any rifle you have (paperwork included in box).  The scope comes with a standard 1/4 MOA turret for use until you send off for your custom dial, or if you wish to shoot various ammunition.

This scope sells MSRPs for $789.99, but sells for $629.99 on MidwayUSA without the sunshade or lens cover (genuine Leupold parts, $100 value).  The scope is professionally mounted in Weaver Tactical picatinny-style rings that are not included in the list price but negotiable.  Condition is like-new; only been mounted for 2 months and 150 rounds.  I'd rather hang on to it than accept a lowball offer, so keep that in mind.  Hopefully this is obvious, but the rifle is NOT included.  Thanks for looking.

postcontent: H&K USP .45ACP W/4 MAGS AND NEW NIGHT SIGHTS INSTALLED BY HK 3 MO AGO USP Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol. All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols. The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols. Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models. The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes. The USP is available in nine trigger/firing mode configurations and three calibers. 9mm, .40 S&W and .45 ACP. Features: •Corrosion proof fiber-reinforced polymer frame •Polygonal bore profile for increased velocity, easier cleaning, and longer barrel life •Can be converted to any of nine trigger firing modes •Corrosion resistant “Hostile Environment” blued finish •Oversized trigger guard for use with gloves •One piece machined slide made from nitro-carburized steel •Universal mounting grooves for installing accessories •Ambidextrous magazine release lever •Extended slide release •Patented Lock-Out Safety device.
